# Security and RBAC invariants

- `super-admin` always has access to all domains.
- Only `super-admin` may add domains, archive/restore/delete domains, or change an admin's domain assignments.
- Admins cannot grant `super-admin` and cannot demote another admin.
- Dashboard assignment requires that the target user already has access to all dashboard domains.
- A viewer can never own a dashboard.
- API keys are not user identities; they are domain-bound, scope-bound service credentials.
- Archived domains reject ingest from every path.
- Internal logs and audit records may contain detailed reasons; external callers must only receive the allowed public error detail.
- Break-glass recovery must stay local-only and never become an HTTP path.
